      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, and i know they love me... but love doesn't make the exhaustion go away. for them, or for me. it just feels like a cycle of misery. sometimes i look at the quiet of the night and think, wouldn't it just be kinder, in the long run, if i wasn't here to cause all this chaos? like, wouldn't they be able to truly breathe again if they didn't have to worry about my next heart flutter or my next fall? it almost feels like a more selfless thing than staying and being a constant weight on their shoulders.",
